      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): surface forum topic names as thread labels",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes #7406. Telegram forum topic names are learned from Telegram topic metadata and exposed as `TopicName`, but native command session metadata did not also expose the topic name as the generic `ThreadLabel`.\n\nAt the same time, the parent group/forum label must remain the conversation label. Replacing `ConversationLabel` with the topic name makes group/forum sessions harder to identify and conflates the group conversation surface with the topic thread surface.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nWhen a forum topic name is known, this change passes that name through the generic thread metadata as `ThreadLabel` while preserving the group/forum value in `ConversationLabel`. `TopicName` remains the Telegram-specific field.\n\nRouting remains unchanged: the session key, conversation id, and `message_thread_id` still carry the chat/topic identifiers, and non-forum groups or unknown topic names keep the previous fallback behavior.\n\n## User Impact\nTelegram forum topic sessions now expose the learned topic name, such as `Deployments`, in thread-aware metadata without hiding the parent group/forum label. Session and routing surfaces can distinguish both pieces of context: the group conversation and the forum topic thread.\n\n## Evidence\nHead commit: `63d0bf8d0688194e74bfe3d36650a6a141b34e9e`.\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-threads.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.session-meta.test.ts` passed: 45 tests.\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.session.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.dm-threads.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-native-commands.session-meta.test.ts` passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` passed.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n\nRegression coverage now asserts:\n\n- forum message context keeps `ConversationLabel` as the forum/group label while setting `TopicName` and `ThreadLabel` to the learned topic name;\n- native Telegram forum commands record both `TopicName` and `ThreadLabel` without replacing the group `ConversationLabel`.\r\n",
